  "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\nWhen running an l2geth instance in replica mode it doesn't seem to be releasing memory when synching which leads to an out of memory condition.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Start a new replica with steps similar to https://github.com/optimisticben/op-replica\r\n2. Wait\r\n3. Observe the process memory usage\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nThe replica should be able to synchronize with the sequencer without restarts.\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\n<img width=\"1339\" alt=\"Screen Shot 2021-08-12 at 8 10 34 AM\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/82120899/129194432-88b6cfbd-9554-4d68-b9a6-4e334cccdf4b.png\">\r\n\r\n**System Specs:**\r\n          resources:\r\n            limits:\r\n              memory: 12Gi\r\n            requests:\r\n              memory: 8Gi\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nExcessive restarts can lead to https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/optimism/issues/1328\r\n",
